               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; title and incipit of daily readings of Text I; refrains of Text I (written out fully or abbreviated); numbers of Pss. in Text II; names of sections of antiphons and their abbreviations (mǝlṭan and mäzmur) in Text II; initial line of Text III; titles of Texts IV and V; names of supplications, antiphons and chants, and their abbreviations (e.g., mästäbqʷǝʿ, mǝlṭan, mäzmur, sälam, ʾaryam) of Text IV; names of feasts of Text IV; names of sections followed by feast names (e.g., wazema zä-mäsqäl, wazema zä-ʾarbaʿǝtu ʾǝnsǝsa) of Text IV; names of antiphons and their abbreviations (e.g., maḫlet, mäzmur, śäläst, sälam, bä-5-tu, ʾabun, ʾaryam, ʾǝsmä lä-ʿaläm, zä-ʾamlakiyä, zä-yǝʾǝze, yǝtbaräk); names of other chants and their abbreviations (e.g., mǝlṭan, mǝsbak, ʿǝzl); intratextual musical signs (e.g., ʿararat mäḥa, ḥaḍä, wäy, läkä sǝ, qädami zema); elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.&#xD;
&#xD;
Two lines (alternating with a black line) on the incipit page of Texts I, IV and V.</rubric>
